&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We identified three potential outcomes:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Centrally underheating kernels, which lead to early cooling catastrophes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Centrally overheating kernels, which lead to unphysically elevated central entropies but ultimately stable clusters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Centrally intermediately heating kernels, which balance a reasonable central entropy
These outcomes were borne out in the simulations depending on how centrally concentrated the AGN heating was.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
